cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.DB

The paper discusses the ranking of users in social networks, specifically Twitter, which involves analyzing the relationships between users and their content. This falls under the sub-category of social networks (cs.SOC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses graph centrality methods, which are commonly used in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the vulnerabilities of ranking algorithms to linking malpractice, which could fall under the sub-category of security and privacy (cs.SI).
